
DOM(Document Object Model)
⇒It is programming interface in web development  that allows us to interact and manipulate (change) the html documents
⇒When the webpage is loaded, the browser creates the DOM of the webpage.
⇒When the html file is loaded in the browser , the javascript cannot understand the html document directly .
⇒DOM : is basically the representation of the same html document but in a tree-like structure composed of objects.
⇒Html DOM allows javascript to access (to get) and modify all the elements in the HTML document.

Key Points:
1)Structure:The DOM represents the structure of the HTML document as tree;each node in the tree represents the element an attribute,text
2)Manipulation : using js,you can interact with elements (buttons,h,p) , we can modify , add, move,remove elements
Change Styles;
3)Event Handling:
4)W3C - World Wide Web Consortium - international standard to implement  the web





In DOM all html elements are defined objects
Property: is a value that you can set to the objects
(Like changing content of an html element)
Method: an action
(like add or delete)

1)getting an element by id
2) getting an element by class:
⇒ returns all the elements having the same class name
⇒ returns in the form of html collection 
3)getting an element by tagname
4)getting an element by queryselector

